 where $\sigma$'s are still Pauli operators on the qubit, and $\tilde{a_{1/2}}$'s are lowering / rising operators on the first or second resonator field in a rotating frame, $\Delta \epsilon$ is (real) detuning of the system, and $\gamma$ characterizes the decay strength of the excited qubit state.

